{"pagelen": 50, "values": [{"update": {"description": "A `disconnect()` call on a `zmq` socket can raise an ~~exception~~ assertion if the other side of the connection is already destroyed. This might happen if you have a fast publisher that publishes some data and then is destroyed right away.\r\n\r\nHow to test the patch?\r\n\r\n* Compile this branch.\r\n* Execute the following test a couple of times. It should **not** fail: \r\n\r\n```\r\n#!c++\r\n\r\n./test/integration/INTEGRATION_twoProcessesPubSub --gtest_filter=*FastPublisher*\r\n```\r\n\r\n* Save the test:\r\n\r\n```\r\n#!c++\r\n\r\ncp ./test/integration/INTEGRATION_twoProcessesPubSub ~\r\n```\r\n\r\n* Compile  `ign-transport1` branch to reproduce the problem.\r\n* Execute the test that you saved before a couple of times and it should eventually fail with an internal zmq assertion: \r\n\r\n```\r\n#!c++\r\n\r\n~/INTEGRATION_twoProcessesPubSub --gtest_filter=*FastPublisher*\r\n```\r\n\r\n* [Trusty](http://build.osrfoundation.org/view/main/view/ignition/job/ignition_transport-ci-pr_any-trusty-amd64/93/) :large_blue_circle:\r\n* [Homebrew](http://build.osrfoundation.org/view/main/view/ignition/job/ignition_transport-ci-pr_any-homebrew-amd64/87/) :large_blue_circle:\r\n* [Windows](http://build.osrfoundation.org/view/main/view/ignition/job/ignition_transport-ci-pr_any-windows7-amd64/177/) :large_blue_circle:", "title": "Remove socket disconnection", "destination": {"commit": {"hash": "2952b7c37584", "type": "commit", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/commit/2952b7c37584.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport/commits/2952b7c37584"}}}, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-transport"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{4249390a-7f55-404b-990d-817ba94cc7ac}ts=1533306"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "ign-transport", "full_name": "igniti